<br>
I cast Manastorm on Nagafen, of course I was banished.  As soon as I zoned through I gated back to prep room and ran into Naggys room, the raid had wiped, but I was there in time for the final wave on my rain spell, some how I got XP along with the message that I had slain Lord Nagafen,and of course I was banished again.  I was confused as hell that I could even get XP, but I gated again and ran back to Naggy's room to make sure no one ninja'd the corpse.<br>
<br>
When I got to Naggy's room what I saw was odd indeed, no corpse for Naggy, and Naggy was no longer up.  It looked like I really did kill Nagafen, I got XP, I got the message, but there was no corpse.  All I can think of is that somewhere in the trivial code that makes Nagafen exile you it is coded that *if* somehow you get the kill as a lvl 54+ character, it just poofs the corpse.  The only alternative I can think of is that somehow someone else looted it in the short time it took me to gate back to prep room, but I dont think that could have happened.<br>
<br>
I guess the bottom line is you *can* kill Nagafen if you are 54+ using rain spells, but I dont know how exactly the coding works, when I did it by mistake the corpse seems to have poofed.  Take it for what it is worth, I dont understand it myself, just explaining what I saw firsthand as best I can. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
